TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {24463=Dart says despite some law enforcement officials giving the OK to carry a concealed weapon without fear of prosecution, Cook County residents shouldn’t expect to carry their guns until at least next February., 24992=With Illinois now the final state to allow concealed carry, law enforcement officials are putting in place the infrastructure to make it happen. Cook County Sheriff Tom Dart joins us on Chicago Tonight at 7:00 pm with details on how gun owners will apply for permits.}
